title: J. B. Davidson scrapbook on trip to Europe for International Conference on Engineering, book 3 of 3
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: This scrapbook consists of photographs taken by J. B. Davidson while attending the International Conference on Engineering in 1935. The photographic subjects are agricultural operations located in Great Britain and other parts of Europe.

title: J. B. Davidson photographs and other materials from the trip to China, 1947-1949
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: A collection of Jay Brownlee Davidson's photographs taken during an International Harvester sponsored trip to China from 1947-1949 to introduce agricultural engineering to the Chinese. A pamphlet, "Committee on Agricultural Engineering for China," is included in the collection and describes the purpose of this committee and Dr. Davidson's appointment as chair. The date 1944 is hand-written on the cover of the pamphlet.

title: J. B. Davidson scrapbook of trip to Russia as member of the American Biro-Bidjan Commission, 1929-1930
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: A scrapbook containing photographs, notes, maps, propaganda, newspaper clippings, and postcards from J. Brownlee Davidson's trip to the Soviet Union in 1929 and a visit of Russian colleagues to Iowa State University in the summer of 1930. The materials document Davidson's work as a member of the American Biro-Bidjan Commission, and feature agricultural practices and machinery, rural and urban life, travel modes, and prominent landmarks.

contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Buckeye ditcher in operation just north of Interurban tracks working toward heating plant. C.& N.W. tracks to the right. Barns and heating plant to the left. Drain extends from heating plant along N. side of Interurban tracks to bridge then crosses there along south side of tracks parallel for a piece thence to Squaw Creek. Quite a bit of ice was in the ground when excavation was done. (above) Picture shows sighting bar and targets at right. (Right) Machine in operation.
